article.headline: Yale 88, Harvard 78
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Caleb Holmes scored 19 points and Casey Hughes 16 as Yale beat Harvard 88-78 on Friday night. Brian Cusworth paced the Crimson attack with a career-high 28 points, giving him 1,023 career points. He also had 10 rebounds. The Bulldogs (6-10, 2-1 Ivy League) are 12-3 against Harvard under current head coach James Jones. Eric Flato and Nick Holmes each added 11 points for Yale. Drew Housman contributed 16 points and Jeremy Lin 10 for the Crimson (8-9, 1-2) who dropped to 3-5 on their home court. The Bulldogs were 58 percent from the floor (28 of 48) and outrebounded Harvard 29-28. Harvard turned the ball over 19 times, good for 23 Bulldog points. Yale opened the second half with a 6-0 run set up when the Harvard bench was called for a technical foul at intermission, when the Crimson had a 40-37 lead. Flato made both free throws and Caleb Holmes scored on the subsequent possession. After cutting the lead to 63-59 following a 3-point play by Cusworth, the Harvard bench was assessed its second technical. That opened the door for a 11-4 Yale charge. Four of the points came on free throws by Caleb Holmes, as the Bulldogs took a commanding 74-63 lead with 3:49 remaining.
